**Documentation for successful run of Apache Kafka data collection**

**Required applications:**

1. USRP UHD and GNU radio has to be installed beforehand.
2. Apache Kafka Services. [Link to download](https://www.apache.org/dyn/closer.cgi?path=/kafka/3.7.0/kafka_2.13-3.7.0.tgz)
3. Apache Kafka Docker image
4. Data Collection GNU Radio File named gnu_radio.py ([github page](https://github.com/Ashwani564/kafka-data-collection))

Steps:

1. Download the file from the link for apache kafka services or you can git clone it from this [github page](https://github.com/Ashwani564/kafka-data-collection):

tar -xzf kafka_2.13-3.7.0.tgz

cd kafka_2.13-3.7.0

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.1 This is the directory you should be in)

1. Start the services on two different terminals:

\# Start the ZooKeeper service

bin/zookeeper-server-start.sh config/zookeeper.properties

\# Start the Kafka broker service

bin/kafka-server-start.sh config/server.properties

1. Without stopping the other. Run the docker container in one container. Note: if you have pulled the required image already. You must skip to the second command below:

docker pull apache/kafka:3.7.0

docker run -p 9092:9092 apache/kafka:3.7.0

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.2: Kafka-server-start.sh (left), zookeeper-server-start.sh (right), docker image(center))

1. If you git clone from the above link, you will get this python file for GNU radio named gnu_radio.py used for data collection.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.3: gnu_radio.py)

1. Run the gnu radio with below command. This file will create the test.txt file. Please note that GNU radio and USRP UHD has to be installed beforehand. Also, the generated file named test.txt can have different size depending upon the amount of data collected.

UHD_IMAGES_DIR=/usr/local/share/uhd/images/ python3 gnu_radio.py

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.4: This should be the output)

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.5: test.txt is created)

1. Run the producer and consumer on two different terminals:

\# Running the producer

bin/connect-standalone.sh config/connect-standalone.properties config/connect-file-source.properties config/connect-file-sink.properties

\# Running the consumer

bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic connect-test --from-beginning

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

(Fig 1.6: Producer (left) and Consumer (right))
